@NODE "Introduction_Node" "Introduction"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}iNTRODUCTIOn@{ub}
@{b}~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

           ... here is the rEAL-sTATUS Door by JiM_bEAM / rEAL ...


  Features:

          - Download Option: the user can download his Status-Info
          - TWO different Status-Infos in ONE door:
            BBS-Status and User-Status
          - all code written in pure C language
          - 68000, 68020+ versions
          - Because of @{b}NO BACKDOOR@{ub} NO RISK
            Disassemble the code if ya don't believe me !!!

          To see all features just install the door and enter "S"
          in the mainprompt of /X


  NEW Features in V2.0:

          - completly reorganised
          - added a main menu
          - 3 different Status-Infos in ONE door:
            Complete Status (BBS + User; long output)
            BBS Status
            User Status
          - view option for every status info
          - download option for every status info
          - Quit option
          - all code written in pure C language
          - 68000, 68020+ versions
          - Because of @{b}NO BACKDOOR@{ub} NO RISK
            Disassemble the code if ya don't believe me !!!

          To see all features just install the door and enter "S"
          in the mainprompt of /X


  NEW in V2.1:

          - fixed a little bug in the "User-status only" design


@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements_Node" "Requirements"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}rEQUIREMENTs@{ub}
@{b}~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

                            Everyone can run it!!!

          - you only need an AMIGA
          - KS2.04 or higher
          - the great AmiExpress V4.x
          - the AEDoor.library V2.4+ in Libs:
          - and rEALdOOR.library in Libs: (included in this archive)
          - a assinged T: directory where "Status.log", "BBSStatus.log",
            "USERStatus.log"-File will be stored for downloading


@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation_Node" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}iNSTALLATIOn@{ub}
@{b}~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

                      The installation is very simple...

   - copy the rEALdOOR.library to Libs:
   - copy the directory rEAL with all the files to DOORS:
   - copy the directory COMMANDS with all the files to BBS:

   ready...


@ENDNODE

@NODE "Working_Node" "Working"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}wORKINg@{ub}
@{b}~~~~~~~@{ub}

   This Door is a replacement for the internal "S"-Command
   in AmiExpress.
   It shows the user info about his Status and about the
   Status of the BBS.
   There is a download option for the user so that he can
   download the Status-Info if he need it.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "Configuration_Node" "Configuration"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}cONFIGURATIOn@{ub}
@{b}~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

  You can configure the door. My door uses the standard /X-Tooltype-Configuration !

  S.info ICON:

  Tooltypes:
     ACCESS
     TYPE
     LOCATION
     STACK
     NAME
     MULTINODE
     BBSNAME
     BBSLOCATION
     HDCOUNT
     HDTYPE
     HDSTORE
     NODES


  ACCESS:
     Pattern : ACCESS= <num>
     Function: Tells /X the access level required to run this module.
               This option is ignored for internal Module options.
     Example : ACCESS=10
               Check for a level about 10 or higher.

  TYPE:
     Pattern : TYPE= < XIM | AIM | TIM | IIM | SIM | MCI >
     Function: This is the type of door you use.
     Example : TYPE=XIM
               For my door the TYPE should be XIM !!!

  LOCATION:
     Pattern : LOCATION= <string>
     Function: Specifies the location of the module
     Example1: LOCATION=DOORS:rEAL/rEAL-sTATUS/rEAL-sTATUS00.exe
               If you are using the version for 68000 CPUs !

     Example2: LOCATION=DOORS:rEAL/rEAL-sTATUS/rEAL-sTATUS020.exe
               If you are using the version for 68020 CPUs !

     Example3: LOCATION=DOORS:rEAL/rEAL-sTATUS/rEAL-sTATUS030.exe
               If you are using the version for 68030 CPUs !

     Example4: LOCATION=DOORS:rEAL/rEAL-sTATUS/rEAL-sTATUS0x0.exe
               If you are using the version for 68040/60 CPUs !

  STACK:
     Pattern : STACK= <Value>
     Function: Specifies the Stack-value for the door and should be
               set to 10000 !
     Example : STACK = 10000
               Sets stack to 10000

  NAME:
     Pattern : NAME= <Doorname>
     Function: Specifies the name to display in the /X-Server window
     Example : NAME = rEAL-sTATUS

  MULTINODE:
     Pattern : MULTINODE= <YES|NO>
     Function: Tells /X if the module may be simultaneously accessed
               from other nodes.

  BBSNAME:
     Pattern : BBSNAME= <Textstring>
     Function: Here you must enter the name of your BBS which should
               be displayed in the Status-Output
     Example : BBSNAME=tHE dUNGEON

  BBSLOCATION:
     Pattern : BBSLOCATION= <Textstring>
     Function: Here you must enter the location of your BBS which should
               be displayed in the Status-Output
     Example : BBSLOCATION=USA

  HDCOUNT:
     Pattern : HDCOUNT= <Number>
     Function: Here you must enter the number of Harddiskdrives you use for
               your BBS and should be displayed in the Status-Output
     Example : HDCOUNT=2
               You use 2 Harddiskdrives for your BBS

  HDTYPE:
     Pattern : HDTYPE= <Textstring>
     Function: Here you must enter what type of Harddiskdrive(s) you use
               for your BBS and should be displayed in the Status-Output
     Example1: HDTYPE=AT-BUS
               You use AT-BUS Harddiskdrive(s)
     Example2: HDTYPE=SCSI
               You use SCSI Harddiskdrive(s)
     Example3: HDTYPE=AT-BUS / SCSI
               You use AT-BUS and SCSI Harddiskdrives

  HDSTORE:
     Pattern : HDSTORE= <Path and filename to uploads-storage>
     Function: Here you must enter the complete path to your
               BBS-Harddiskdrives where uploads are stored
               !! IT'S IMPORTANT FOR DISPLAYING THE "Free HD Space" !!
     Example1: HDSTORE=BBS:
               All uploads are stored in "BBS:"
     Example2: HDSTORE=BBS:Uploads/
               All uploads are stored in "BBS:Uploads"
               !! DON'T FORGET THE "/" IF THE PATH IS A DIRECTORY !!

  NODES:
     Pattern : NODES= <Number>
     Function: The number of total nodes your BBS supports
     Example : NODES=5
               Your BBS supports 5 Nodes (0,1,2,3,4)


@ENDNODE

