@NODE "emailware_Node" "emailware"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}E-mAILWARe ??@{ub}
@{b}~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

   You will ask yourself what's meant by "E-mAILWARe".
   Well, because i would like to know who is using my door for his BBS
   i decided to release this door under "E-mAILWARe".
   That means if you interested in this door and want to use it in your
   BBS, you have to send me a e-mail with the Registerstring
   (Handle or Handle & Group; up to 15 characters long)
   you would like to have inserted into the Registertext "Registered to:"
   in the Design.
   Otherwise the Registertext will look like this:
   Registered to: UNREGISTERED!!!

   If you register the Registertext will look like this for example:

   Registered to: JiM_bEAM^rEAL!

   The door is fully functional without the Registerstring too.

   My e-mail: jim_beam@bigfoot.de
              jim.real@usa.net


@ENDNODE

